        <p>b-Included pretax charges of $ 5.8 million and after-tax charges of $ 3.5 million, or 11 cents a share, for preopening and gaming development costs for the three months ended June 30. Of this amount, pretax charges of $ 4.8 million and after-tax charges of $ 2.9 million, or 9 cents a share, relate to preopening costs associated with the Mesquite, Nev., and Maryland Heights, Mo., facilities and the Star Riverboat Casino for the three months ended June 30. The company's common stock was split 3-for-2 on May 19 to stockholders of record on May 8. All issued and outstanding shares and earnings per share amounts have been restated to give effect to the stock split. Share earnings are fully diluted.</p>
